Johanna Powell was reported missing on Saturday after a cruise boat she was on hit a rock and sank in the Mekong river . 
  The 37-year-old was sailing along the river in Laos with three friends when the accident happened . 
  Crew and passengers swam to safety but she disappeared in the strong current . 
  Emergency services in Laos have recovered a body in the search for Ms Powell . 
  She was a picture editor working for BBC Wales and was on holiday in Laos . 
 